CCM.Name: 181 Drum Pitch Coarse
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Pitch Coarse] Change the Pitch Coarse of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 182 Drum Pitch Fine
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Pitch Fine] Change the Pitch Fine of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 183 Drum Level
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Level] Change the Level of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 184 Drum Panpot
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Panpot] Change the Panpot of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64. Value 0 means Random.

CCM.Name: 185 Drum Reverb
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Reverb] Change the Reverb Level of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 186 Drum Chorus
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Chorus] Change the Chorus Level of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 187 Drum Variation
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Variation] Change the Variation Effect Level of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 188 Drum LPF
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum LPF Cutoff Frequency] Change the LPF Cutoff Freqency of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 189 Drum Resonance
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum LPF Resonance] Change the LPF Cutoff Resonance of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 191 Drum Attack
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Attack Rate] Change the Attack Rate of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 192 Drum Decay
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum Decay Rate] Change both Decay and Release Rate of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: 193 Drum EQ L-Freq

CCM.Name: 194 Drum EQ L-Gain

CCM.Name: 195 Drum EQ H-Freq

CCM.Name: 196 Drum EQ H-Gain
CCM.Memo: [NRPN Drum EQ High Gain] Change the EQ High Gain of the Note (assigned with the Gate). Default = 64

CCM.Name: note:Drum track as XGSupport
CCM.Memo: You can also program the non-drum track to Main/Add Drum Track.\nChoose the non-drum Program Change from SOUND LIST.

CCM.Name: note:Marker list
CCM.Memo:
If you edit Style File,
type the following words verbatim into the beginning of the section as 'Mark' :
Main A
Main B
Main C
Main D
Fill In AA
Fill In BB
Fill In CC
Fill In DD
Fill In BA
Intro A
Intro B
Intro C
Ending A
Ending B
Ending C

CCM.Name: note:From 2nd bar !
CCM.Memo: The notes should be written from the second bar.

CCM.Name: note:One time signature
CCM.Memo:
Each Style File can have only one time signature. 
If you want to program irregular time,
 1. you have to make the Styles for each time signature
 2. or combine some time signatures into one Style (e.g. 3/4 + 5/8 => 11/8)
